cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about object detection using convolutional neural networks (CNN) and focuses on improving the efficiency and accuracy of multi-scale object detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new method for computing feature maps, which involves a recurrent rolling out mechanism, which suggests that it could also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a scale-forecast network and a landmark retracing network, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.MM (Multimedia), respectively. Finally, the paper uses a unified CNN framework for end-to-end training, which could also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
